text: Ozerki () is a rural locality (a village) in Shevchenkovsky Selsoviet, Meleuzovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 127 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 10 km from Meleuz, 2 km from Antonovka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Meleuzovsky District
title: Ozerki, Meleuzovsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
